    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Techniques characterized by indentations or holes that are applied using punches, and forming texture or designs. Examples of punchwork are in leather items, wooden items such as altarpieces, metalwork, or paper crafts.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
